The paper focuses on analyzing and improving deep neural networks, which is a common topic in the machine learning community. Specifically, the paper proposes a new metric and statistical framework for evaluating gradient norm equality in DNNs. This topic falls under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), neural networks (cs.NE), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and signal processing (cs.SI).
